<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"MigrationguideforSpringframeworkupgradeforV4APIplatform-ProblemSt=
atement:">Problem Statement :</h3>
<p>As part of the upcoming Janus release, we will be migrating our platform=
 from Spring 5 to Spring 6. Although the v4 ecosystem relies on Springboot =
BOM to pull the spring6 libraries into the nutanix ecosystem (PC or AOS), t=
he platform team will eventually migrate to consume springboot-3.5.x built =
on Spring 6.2.x framework. All the underlying dependencies will need to pul=
l the appropriate version of spring in order to ensure the end goal of upgr=
ading the framework throughout the v4 ecosystem is met.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>The platform team will lead the migration effort. An initial POC was don=
e by the platform team to identify the scope of work needed. We request sup=
port from the NRPC controller teams to help address any compilation or unit=
 test issues that may arise.This documents provide a comprehensive guidelin=
es=E2=80=82and potential changes need to fix the UTs or any compilations is=
sues. For GRPC controllers, the impact is minimal, and we mainly need your =
assistance in testing the changes.</p>
